content: Will rate it 5 stars when options for non-secretor are added!  :)  Would also like it if I could pull up recipes as part of the app rather than being directed to the website, which displays in very small text on my phone.
replyContent: Regarding secretor status option, it's there. Simply select Secretor Status from main page. Then, leave Non-Secretor setting Off if you are a secretor; turn it ON if you are a non secretor. That's it. You can verify your selection by looking at Blood Type in the lower left hand corner - you will see your secretor status selection in parenthesis.

replyContent:
Thank you for trying our Blood Type Diet App.
Please note that Eat Right For Your Type was written over 15 years ago and there have been updates that are reflected in the Blood Type Diet App (noted in app's FAQ). Dr. Peter D'Adamo has the most current updates here: http://www.dadamo.com/typebase4/typeindexer.htm  - these are the same as in the App.

replyContent: We are sorry you are disappointed. While our app does contain links to Dr. Peter D'Adamo's web sites, that is only a small part of the App. Contained within the app are food categories, individual and family food list, secretor selector, and more which you can see in the screenshots. It's intended as a convenience when you are out.
